==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gonfalonier
<hw>Gon`fa*lon*ier"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>gonfalonier</ets>: cf. It. <ets>gonfaloniere</ets>.]</ety> <def>He
who bears the gonfalon; a standard bearer</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>An officer at Rome who bears the standard of the Church.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The chief magistrate of any one of several republics
in medi⟦ae⟧veal Italy.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A Turkish general, and
standard keeper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gong</ent>⟦br⟧
